description:
Pivot Cycles, BH Bikes Demo with Millcreek Bicycles
9/4/2011
10:00 am - 4:00pm
Rotary Glen Park at the mouth of Emigration Canyon
Contact: Millcreek Bicycles 801 278-1500
www.millcreekcycles.com
course: After choosing a demo bike, riders may ride up Emigration Canyon or hop on the Bonneville Shoreline Trail.
registration: No registration is required, only a valid ID and Credit/Debit Card.
directions: From I80, take Foothill Blvd north to Sunnyside Ave. Turn East on Sunnyside, drive to the mouth of Emigration Canyon.  Rotary Glen Park is located on the south side of the road before entering Emigration Canyon.

title: LOTOJA CLASSIC
description: Almost 30 years ago, LOTOJA\'s creation was inspired and patterned after the one-day European road classics.  LOTOJA\'s course is unparalleled in distance and beauty.  Cyclists come from all over the U.S. to test their physical and mental stamina on a 206-mile course that climbs and descends three mountain passes with almost 10,000 feet of climbing.
course: LOTOJA starts in Logan, Utah, weaves its way north through southeastern Idaho, and finishes in the shadows of the Teton Mountain Range at Jackson Hole, Wyoming.  Total distance is 206 miles over three states.  Visit www.lotojaclassic.com for more course information and detailed maps.
registration: For information and online registration visit www.lotojaclassic.com
notes: This year is the 29th Annual LOTOJA CLASSIC.
